ource=3Dcustomer.io&utm_term=3Df6c60617da42abd12a ), Peacock has racked up =
more than $9 billion in losses since its 2019 launch and is projected to lo=
se more than $1 billion this year, just as the cost of
a new NBA rights deal kicks in. Despite that, as MoffettNathanson analyst C=
raig Moffett argued, =E2=80=9CThere was no fall-off in subscribers after th=
e end of the Summer Olympics. That=E2=80=99s a win.=E2=80=9D

=C2=A0

Is it, though? The only content that meaningfully perks the feathers at Pea=
cock is live sports. And, more specifically, NBC Sports programming that is=
 only on Peacock. That=E2=80=99s incredibly expensive, of course, and
the leagues and their fans don=E2=80=99t love having to track down games on=
